<!-- Why Net Income Can Be Misleading -->
<div class="ni-content-section">
  <h2>Why Net Income Can Be Misleading</h2>
  <p>Net income is the most cited profitability metric, but it has real limitations that every investor should understand. Here are the three biggest traps:</p>

  <div class="ni-warning-box">
    <h4>⚠️ One-Time Items</h4>
    <ul>
      <li>Asset sales, lawsuit settlements, and restructuring charges can inflate or deflate net income in a single quarter</li>
      <li>A company might report record net income from selling a building — not from growing its core business</li>
      <li>Always check if earnings are "recurring" or "non-recurring" in the footnotes</li>
    </ul>
  </div>

  <div class="ni-warning-box">
    <h4>⚠️ Depreciation & Amortization</h4>
    <ul>
      <li>Companies with heavy capital expenditures (factories, equipment) show lower net income due to depreciation — even if cash flow is strong</li>
      <li>Two companies with identical cash flows can report very different net income depending on their depreciation schedules</li>
      <li>This is why <a href="/ebitda-calculator/" style="color:var(--ni-accent);">EBITDA</a> is popular — it adds back these non-cash charges</li>
    </ul>
  </div>

  <div class="ni-warning-box">
    <h4>⚠️ Stock-Based Compensation (SBC)</h4>
    <ul>
      <li>Tech companies often pay employees with stock options, which are expensed on the income statement</li>
      <li>SBC reduces net income but doesn't require actual cash spending — it dilutes existing shareholders instead</li>
      <li>Some companies report "adjusted net income" that excludes SBC, making their profitability look much better</li>
    </ul>
  </div>
</div>

<!-- 5 Key Insights -->
<div class="ni-content-section">
  <h2>5 Key Insights About Net Income</h2>
  <div class="ni-insights-grid">
    <div class="ni-insight-card">
      <div class="ni-insight-num">1</div>
      <div class="ni-insight-text"><strong>Net income drives stock prices.</strong> Earnings per share (EPS) is derived from net income, and it's the single most important factor in stock valuation. When a company "beats earnings," it means net income exceeded expectations.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="ni-insight-card">
      <div class="ni-insight-num">2</div>
      <div class="ni-insight-text"><strong>Margins matter more than absolute numbers.</strong> A $10B company earning $1B (10% margin) is more efficient than a $100B company earning $5B (5% margin). Always compare net profit margins, not just raw net income figures.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="ni-insight-card">
      <div class="ni-insight-num">3</div>
      <div class="ni-insight-text"><strong>Net income funds dividends.</strong> Companies can only sustainably pay dividends from net income. The payout ratio (dividends ÷ net income) tells you whether a dividend is safe. A ratio above 100% means the company is paying more than it earns.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="ni-insight-card">
      <div class="ni-insight-num">4</div>
      <div class="ni-insight-text"><strong>Negative net income isn't always bad.</strong> High-growth companies like Amazon were unprofitable for years while reinvesting every dollar into growth. The question is whether losses are strategic (investing in future growth) or structural (bad business model).</div>
    </div>
    <div class="ni-insight-card">
      <div class="ni-insight-num">5</div>
      <div class="ni-insight-text"><strong>Look at the trend, not a single year.</strong> One year of high net income could be a fluke. Three to five years of consistently growing net income is a strong signal of business quality. Use our trend analyzer above to measure compound annual growth.</div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

<!-- FAQ Section -->
<div class="ni-faq-section">
  <h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>

  <div class="ni-faq-item">
    <div class="ni-faq-q" onclick="toggleNiFaq(this)">
      <span>What is net income and how do you calculate it?</span>
      <span class="ni-faq-arrow">▼</span>
    </div>
    <div class="ni-faq-a">Net income is the total profit a company earns after subtracting all expenses from revenue. The formula is: Net Income = Revenue − Cost of Goods Sold − Operating Expenses − Interest − Taxes. It is also called the bottom line, net profit, or net earnings, and appears at the very bottom of the income statement.</div>
  </div>

  <div class="ni-faq-item">
    <div class="ni-faq-q" onclick="toggleNiFaq(this)">
      <span>What is the difference between net income and gross profit?</span>
      <span class="ni-faq-arrow">▼</span>
    </div>
    <div class="ni-faq-a">Gross profit only subtracts the cost of goods sold (COGS) from revenue, showing production efficiency. Net income goes further by also subtracting operating expenses, interest, and taxes. Gross profit is always higher than net income because it excludes many additional expenses.</div>
  </div>

  <div class="ni-faq-item">
    <div class="ni-faq-q" onclick="toggleNiFaq(this)">
      <span>What is a good net profit margin?</span>
      <span class="ni-faq-arrow">▼</span>
    </div>
    <div class="ni-faq-a">A good net profit margin varies by industry. Software companies often achieve 20-30%, while retail and grocery stores operate at 2-5%. The S&P 500 average is approximately 10-12%. Always compare within the same sector for meaningful analysis.</div>
  </div>

  <div class="ni-faq-item">
    <div class="ni-faq-q" onclick="toggleNiFaq(this)">
      <span>Why can net income be misleading?</span>
      <span class="ni-faq-arrow">▼</span>
    </div>
    <div class="ni-faq-a">Net income can be misleading because it includes one-time items (asset sales, lawsuit settlements), non-cash charges (depreciation, stock-based compensation), and can be affected by accounting choices. Always look at the quality of earnings, not just the number.</div>
  </div>

  <div class="ni-faq-item">
    <div class="ni-faq-q" onclick="toggleNiFaq(this)">
      <span>How is net income different from EBITDA?</span>
      <span class="ni-faq-arrow">▼</span>
    </div>
    <div class="ni-faq-a">EBITDA strips out interest, taxes, depreciation, and amortization to focus on operating cash flow. Net income includes all of these. EBITDA is better for comparing companies with different capital structures, while net income shows the actual bottom-line profit after all obligations. Learn more with our <a href="/ebitda-calculator/" style="color:var(--ni-accent);">EBITDA Calculator</a>.</div>
  </div>
</div>

<script is:inline src="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/chart.js"></script>

<script is:inline>
  var waterfallChartInstance = null;
  var trendChartInstance = null;
  var sectorChartInstance = null;

  function fmtCurrency(n) {
    if (n === undefined || n === null || isNaN(n)) return "$0";
    var abs = Math.abs(n);
    var sign = n < 0 ? "-" : "";
    if (abs >= 1e9) return sign + "$" + (abs / 1e9).toFixed(2) + "B";
    if (abs >= 1e6) return sign + "$" + (abs / 1e6).toFixed(2) + "M";
    if (abs >= 1e3) return sign + "$" + (abs / 1e3).toFixed(1) + "K";
    return sign + "$" + abs.toFixed(0);
  }

  function fmtPct(n) {
    if (n === undefined || n === null || isNaN(n)) return "0.0%";
    return n.toFixed(1) + "%";
  }

  function valClass(n) {
    return n >= 0 ? "ni-pos" : "ni-neg";
  }

  /* ==================== Net Income Calculator ==================== */
  function calcNetIncome() {
    var revenue = parseFloat(document.getElementById("ni-revenue").value) || 0;
    var cogs = parseFloat(document.getElementById("ni-cogs").value) || 0;
    var opex = parseFloat(document.getElementById("ni-opex").value) || 0;
    var interest = parseFloat(document.getElementById("ni-interest").value) || 0;
    var taxRate = parseFloat(document.getElementById("ni-taxrate").value) || 0;

    if (revenue === 0) { alert("Please enter revenue."); return; }

    var grossProfit = revenue - cogs;
    var operatingIncome = grossProfit - opex;
    var preTaxIncome = operatingIncome - interest;
    var taxes = preTaxIncome > 0 ? preTaxIncome * (taxRate / 100) : 0;
    var netIncome = preTaxIncome - taxes;

    var grossMargin = (grossProfit / revenue) * 100;
    var operatingMargin = (operatingIncome / revenue) * 100;
    var preTaxMargin = (preTaxIncome / revenue) * 100;
    var netMargin = (netIncome / revenue) * 100;

    var html = "";
    html += '<div class="ni-result-row"><span class="ni-result-label">Revenue</span><span class="ni-result-val">' + fmtCurrency(revenue) + '</span></div>';
    html += '<div class="ni-result-row"><span class="ni-result-label">− COGS</span><span class="ni-result-val ni-neg">' + fmtCurrency(cogs) + '</span></div>';
    html += '<div class="ni-result-row"><span class="ni-result-label">= Gross Profit (' + fmtPct(grossMargin) + ' margin)</span><span class="ni-result-val ' + valClass(grossProfit) + '">' + fmtCurrency(grossProfit) + '</span></div>';
    html += '<div class="ni-result-row"><span class="ni-result-label">− Operating Expenses</span><span class="ni-result-val ni-neg">' + fmtCurrency(opex) + '</span></div>';
    html += '<div class="ni-result-row"><span class="ni-result-label">= Operating Income (' + fmtPct(operatingMargin) + ' margin)</span><span class="ni-result-val ' + valClass(operatingIncome) + '">' + fmtCurrency(operatingIncome) + '</span></div>';
    html += '<div class="ni-result-row"><span class="ni-result-label">− Interest Expense</span><span class="ni-result-val ni-neg">' + fmtCurrency(interest) + '</span></div>';
    html += '<div class="ni-result-row"><span class="ni-result-label">= Pre-Tax Income (' + fmtPct(preTaxMargin) + ' margin)</span><span class="ni-result-val ' + valClass(preTaxIncome) + '">' + fmtCurrency(preTaxIncome) + '</span></div>';
    html += '<div class="ni-result-row"><span class="ni-result-label">− Taxes (' + fmtPct(taxRate) + ' rate)</span><span class="ni-result-val ni-neg">' + fmtCurrency(taxes) + '</span></div>';
    html += '<div class="ni-result-row" style="border-top:2px solid var(--ni-accent);padding-top:0.8rem;"><span class="ni-result-label" style="font-weight:700;color:#e6edf3;">Net Income (' + fmtPct(netMargin) + ' margin)</span><span class="ni-result-val ' + valClass(netIncome) + '" style="font-size:1.2rem;">' + fmtCurrency(netIncome) + '</span></div>';

    var box = document.getElementById("ni-result");
    box.innerHTML = html;
    box.style.display = "block";

    updateWaterfallChart(revenue, grossProfit, operatingIncome, netIncome);
  }

  /* ==================== Profit Margin Calculator ==================== */
  function calcMargins() {
    var revenue = parseFloat(document.getElementById("pm-revenue").value) || 0;
    var gross = parseFloat(document.getElementById("pm-gross").value) || 0;
    var operating = parseFloat(document.getElementById("pm-operating").value) || 0;
    var net = parseFloat(document.getElementById("pm-net").value) || 0;

    if (revenue === 0) { alert("Please enter revenue."); return; }

    var grossMargin = (gross / revenue) * 100;
    var opMargin = (operating / revenue) * 100;
    var netMargin = (net / revenue) * 100;

    var rating = "Low";
    var ratingColor = "var(--ni-negative)";
    if (netMargin >= 20) { rating = "Excellent"; ratingColor = "var(--ni-positive)"; }
    else if (netMargin >= 10) { rating = "Strong"; ratingColor = "var(--ni-positive)"; }
    else if (netMargin >= 5) { rating = "Average"; ratingColor = "var(--ni-warning)"; }

    var html = "";
    html += '<div class="ni-result-row"><span class="ni-result-label">Gross Profit Margin</span><span class="ni-result-val ' + valClass(grossMargin) + '">' + fmtPct(grossMargin) + '</span></div>';
    html += '<div class="ni-result-row"><span class="ni-result-label">Operating Profit Margin</span><span class="ni-result-val ' + valClass(opMargin) + '">' + fmtPct(opMargin) + '</span></div>';
    html += '<div class="ni-result-row"><span class="ni-result-label">Net Profit Margin</span><span class="ni-result-val ' + valClass(netMargin) + '">' + fmtPct(netMargin) + '</span></div>';
    html += '<div class="ni-result-row" style="border-top:2px solid var(--ni-accent);padding-top:0.8rem;"><span class="ni-result-label">Profitability Rating</span><span class="ni-result-val" style="color:' + ratingColor + ';">' + rating + '</span></div>';

    var box = document.getElementById("pm-result");
    box.innerHTML = html;
    box.style.display = "block";
  }

  /* ==================== Waterfall Chart ==================== */
  function updateWaterfallChart(revenue, grossProfit, operatingIncome, netIncome) {
    var ctx = document.getElementById("waterfallChart").getContext("2d");
    if (waterfallChartInstance) waterfallChartInstance.destroy();

    var cogsVal = revenue - grossProfit;
    var opexVal = grossProfit - operatingIncome;
    var belowOp = operatingIncome - netIncome;

    waterfallChartInstance = new Chart(ctx, {
      type: "bar",
      data: {
        labels: ["Revenue", "COGS", "Gross Profit", "OpEx", "Operating Income", "Interest & Tax", "Net Income"],
        datasets: [
          {
            label: "Base",
            data: [0, netIncome < 0 ? 0 : 0, 0, netIncome < 0 ? 0 : 0, 0, netIncome < 0 ? 0 : 0, 0],
            backgroundColor: "transparent",
            borderWidth: 0
          },
          {
            label: "Base (hidden)",
            data: [0, grossProfit, 0, operatingIncome, 0, netIncome > 0 ? netIncome : 0, 0],
            backgroundColor: "transparent",
            borderWidth: 0
          },
          {
            label: "Value",
            data: [revenue, cogsVal, grossProfit, opexVal, operatingIncome, belowOp, netIncome > 0 ? netIncome : 0],
            backgroundColor: [
              "#4a8fe7",
              "#ef4444",
              "#10b981",
              "#ef4444",
              "#10b981",
              "#ef4444",
              netIncome >= 0 ? "#10b981" : "#ef4444"
            ],
            borderRadius: 4
          }
        ]
      },
      options: {
        responsive: true,
        maintainAspectRatio: true,
        plugins: {
          legend: { display: false },
          tooltip: {
            callbacks: {
              label: function(context) {
                if (context.datasetIndex < 2) return "";
                return fmtCurrency(context.raw);
              }
            }
          }
        },
        scales: {
          x: { stacked: true, grid: { display: false }, ticks: { color: "#8b949e" } },
          y: {
            stacked: true,
            grid: { color: "#30363d" },
            ticks: {
              color: "#8b949e",
              callback: function(val) { return fmtCurrency(val); }
            }
          }
        }
      }
    });
  }

  /* ==================== Trend Analyzer ==================== */
  function calcTrend() {
    var vals = [];
    var y1 = parseFloat(document.getElementById("trend-y1").value);
    var y2 = parseFloat(document.getElementById("trend-y2").value);
    var y3 = parseFloat(document.getElementById("trend-y3").value);
    var y4 = parseFloat(document.getElementById("trend-y4").value);
    var y5 = parseFloat(document.getElementById("trend-y5").value);

    if (!isNaN(y1)) vals.push(y1);
    if (!isNaN(y2)) vals.push(y2);
    if (!isNaN(y3)) vals.push(y3);
    if (!isNaN(y4)) vals.push(y4);
    if (!isNaN(y5)) vals.push(y5);

    if (vals.length < 3) { alert("Please enter at least 3 years of data."); return; }

    var first = vals[0];
    var last = vals[vals.length - 1];
    var years = vals.length - 1;

    var cagr = 0;
    var direction = "Flat";
    var dirColor = "var(--ni-warning)";

    if (first > 0 && last > 0) {
      cagr = (Math.pow(last / first, 1 / years) - 1) * 100;
    } else if (first < 0 && last > 0) {
      cagr = 999;
    } else if (first > 0 && last < 0) {
      cagr = -999;
    }

    if (cagr > 5) { direction = "Growing ↑"; dirColor = "var(--ni-positive)"; }
    else if (cagr < -5) { direction = "Declining ↓"; dirColor = "var(--ni-negative)"; }
    else { direction = "Flat →"; dirColor = "var(--ni-warning)"; }

    var totalChange = first !== 0 ? ((last - first) / Math.abs(first)) * 100 : 0;

    var html = "";
    html += '<div class="ni-result-row"><span class="ni-result-label">Starting Net Income</span><span class="ni-result-val">' + fmtCurrency(first) + '</span></div>';
    html += '<div class="ni-result-row"><span class="ni-result-label">Ending Net Income</span><span class="ni-result-val">' + fmtCurrency(last) + '</span></div>';
    html += '<div class="ni-result-row"><span class="ni-result-label">Total Change</span><span class="ni-result-val ' + valClass(totalChange) + '">' + fmtPct(totalChange) + '</span></div>';
    if (Math.abs(cagr) < 900) {
      html += '<div class="ni-result-row"><span class="ni-result-label">CAGR</span><span class="ni-result-val ' + valClass(cagr) + '">' + fmtPct(cagr) + '</span></div>';
    }
    html += '<div class="ni-result-row" style="border-top:2px solid var(--ni-accent);padding-top:0.8rem;"><span class="ni-result-label">Trend Direction</span><span class="ni-result-val" style="color:' + dirColor + ';">' + direction + '</span></div>';

    var box = document.getElementById("trend-result");
    box.innerHTML = html;
    box.style.display = "block";

    var wrap = document.getElementById("trend-chart-wrap");
    wrap.style.display = "block";

    var labels = [];
    for (var i = 0; i < vals.length; i++) { labels.push("Year " + (i + 1)); }

    var ctx = document.getElementById("trendChart").getContext("2d");
    if (trendChartInstance) trendChartInstance.destroy();

    trendChartInstance = new Chart(ctx, {
      type: "line",
      data: {
        labels: labels,
        datasets: [{
          label: "Net Income",
          data: vals,
          borderColor: "#4a8fe7",
          backgroundColor: "rgba(74,143,231,0.1)",
          fill: true,
          tension: 0.3,
          pointRadius: 6,
          pointBackgroundColor: "#4a8fe7",
          pointBorderColor: "#fff",
          pointBorderWidth: 2
        }]
      },
      options: {
        responsive: true,
        maintainAspectRatio: true,
        plugins: {
          legend: { display: false },
          tooltip: {
            callbacks: {
              label: function(context) { return fmtCurrency(context.raw); }
            }
          }
        },
        scales: {
          x: { grid: { display: false }, ticks: { color: "#8b949e" } },
          y: {
            grid: { color: "#30363d" },
            ticks: {
              color: "#8b949e",
              callback: function(val) { return fmtCurrency(val); }
            }
          }
        }
      }
    });
  }

  /* ==================== Sector Chart ==================== */
  function initSectorChart() {
    var ctx = document.getElementById("sectorChart").getContext("2d");
    if (sectorChartInstance) sectorChartInstance.destroy();

    var sectors = [
      "Technology",
      "Real Estate",
      "Financials",
      "Healthcare",
      "Communication Services",
      "Industrials",
      "Consumer Staples",
      "Utilities",
      "Materials",
      "Energy",
      "Consumer Discretionary"
    ];
    var margins = [23.5, 20.1, 18.4, 13.2, 12.8, 9.5, 8.2, 7.8, 7.1, 6.8, 5.9];
    var colors = margins.map(function(m) {
      if (m >= 15) return "#10b981";
      if (m >= 10) return "#4a8fe7";
      if (m >= 7) return "#f59e0b";
      return "#ef4444";
    });

    sectorChartInstance = new Chart(ctx, {
      type: "bar",
      data: {
        labels: sectors,
        datasets: [{
          label: "Net Profit Margin (%)",
          data: margins,
          backgroundColor: colors,
          borderRadius: 4
        }]
      },
      options: {
        indexAxis: "y",
        responsive: true,
        maintainAspectRatio: true,
        plugins: {
          legend: { display: false },
          tooltip: {
            callbacks: {
              label: function(context) { return context.raw + "% net margin"; }
            }
          }
        },
        scales: {
          x: {
            grid: { color: "#30363d" },
            ticks: {
              color: "#8b949e",
              callback: function(val) { return val + "%"; }
            }
          },
          y: {
            grid: { display: false },
            ticks: { color: "#c9d1d9" }
          }
        }
      }
    });
  }

  /* ==================== FAQ Toggle ==================== */
  function toggleNiFaq(el) {
    var item = el.parentElement;
    var isOpen = item.className.indexOf("open") !== -1;
    if (isOpen) {
      item.className = item.className.replace(" open", "");
    } else {
      item.className = item.className + " open";
    }
  }

  /* ==================== Init ==================== */
  if (document.readyState === "loading") {
    document.addEventListener("DOMContentLoaded", initSectorChart);
  } else {
    initSectorChart();
  }
</script>

</SiteLayout>
